AU  - Gode, Dhananjay K.
AU  - Sunder, Shyam
T1  - What Makes Markets Allocationally Efficient?*
PY  - 1997
Y1  - 1997/05/01
DO  - 10.1162/003355397555307
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 112
IS  - 2
SP  - 603
EP  - 630
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - What determines the allocative efficiency of markets? Why are double auctions, even with untrained human traders, allocationally efficient? We provide a simple explanation for these complex phenomena by showing how externally observable rules that define a market cause high allocative efficiency when individuals remain within the confines of these rules. We also show how the oft-ignored shape of extramarginal demand and supply affects efficiency by influencing the inverse relationship between the magnitude of efficiency loss and its probability.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355397555307
ER  - 



